    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": "## 4. Stiff System: Van der Pol Oscillator (BDF)\n\n$$\\dot{x} = v, \\qquad \\dot{v} = \\mu(1 - x^2) v - x$$\n\nWith $\\mu = 10$ the system is moderately stiff — sharp transitions between slow drift and fast jumps. We use `method=bdf` to handle the stiffness.",
      "metadata": {}
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": "tspan4 : np_linspace(0.0, 40.0, 2000)$\nres4 : np_odeint(\n  [vv, 10*(1 - xx^2)*vv - xx],\n  [t, xx, vv], [2.0, 0.0], tspan4, 1e-8, 1e-8, bdf)$\n\nt4 : np_slice(res4, all, 0)$\nx4 : np_slice(res4, all, 1)$\nv4 : np_slice(res4, all, 2)$",
      "metadata": {},
      "execution_count": 24,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": "ax_draw2d(\n  color=\"blue\", line_width=1,\n  lines(np_to_list(t4), np_to_list(x4)),\n  title=\"Van der Pol (mu=10, BDF)\", xlabel=\"t\", ylabel=\"x\",\n  grid=true\n)$",
      "metadata": {},
      "execution_count": 25,
      "outputs": [
        {
